A mother who gave birth on a Manhattan sidewalk described her baby's dramatic arrival - and how one impatient New Yorker pinched the cab she was trying to take to hospital. 

Polly McCourt, 39, went into labor at around 4pm on Monday and was being helped to the street corner by her doorman Anton Rudovic  to hail a taxi.

However when they got to the corner of East 68th Street and Third Avenue - a woman jumped in front of her and stole the cab.

